creator: Otherweb
descriptionHtml:
Do you think ads are annoying? Do you hate fake news and clickbait?

Many people have this gnawing feeling that the internet stopped making sense at some point, and that perhaps we need to scrap everything and start over.

So.. we did.

We built a new platform for people who care about what they put into their brain. A smarter way to be informed. A sensemaking instrument for sensible people. The other web.

Here’s how it works.

We aggregate different types of content from thousands of sources. For example:
- Tech news
- Science news
- World news
- Local news
- Commentary and opinion columns
- Op ed articles
- Research studies
- Online courses
- Podcasts
- Encyclopedia entries

We apply 20+ NLP filters to weed out the junk, and attach a nutrition label to each article.

We use a summarizer AI model to generate a new headline and a bullet-point summary of each article - so you can get the gist of it, faster, and without clickbait.

We use a categorizer AI model to sort items by topic and to separate news columns from opinion columns. This way you can follow specific topics that interest you with complete control and transparency.

We create a two-dimensional way to navigate information -
So if you encounter an interesting concept in a news article and want to learn more, you can search for it in research studies or on wikipedia, or find an online course or a book on this topic. The same concept can be explored across different levels of rigor, and there’s no need to type - just highlight any text you see and search for it in any medium you like. Drill down, zoom in, zoom out, peak sideways.. explore!

What you get as a result is something truly remarkable.

A walled garden -- insulated from the noise of the outside world. A customizable feed of pure, pristine information, filtered and summarized by cutting edge artificial intelligence models. A smarter news reader app, combined with an education platform, that keeps you grounded, balanced, calm and informed.

The Otherweb has no ads, no clickbait, no fake news, no propaganda, no misinformation, no political bias, no sensationalism, and no junk.

Only high quality information and unbiased reporting, supported by artificial intelligence, scientific rigor, and complete transparency.

Join the community.

title: Otherweb

creator: Otherweb
descriptionHtml:
Stay informed with the latest news on science, technology, business, world, entertainment, politics, health, and sports – from hundreds of curated global sources – with no noise, junk, ads, or clickbait.

Brought to you by a Public Benefit Corporation whose bylaws prioritize information quality above profits.

OUR AI MODELS FILTER JUNK OUT
Our 20 cutting-edge technology models, with source code and datasets open to the public, offer full transparency and no hidden biases. We use the latest AI science to effectively detect (and filter) misinformation, disinformation, propaganda, and clickbait offer you the top 1% of all articles about science, technology, and other categories.

CUSTOMIZE YOUR EXPERIENCE AND CONTROL YOUR FEED
You have complete control over sources, categories, and the number of articles in each category (e.g. science, technology, business, world, entertainment, politics, health, and sports). You can enable or disable publications as you see fit. You can see how we've curated the feed to your preferences and manually adjust everything we did. There are no black boxes - you are in control.

SEE THINGS THAT MAINSTREAM NEWS OUTLETS RARELY COVER
Most news outlets emphasize sensational, infuriating and depressing news items. We focus on the things that really matter instead: world events and global shifts; science, cutting-edge studies and peer-reviewed research; tech, gadgets and innovation; and more. We really love science & tech. We sincerely believe that science & tech affects your life in a way that overblown controversies and political polls do not. Science & tech are positive and uplifting. They show the best of the human spirit and help us get informed and stay informed.

A SLICK USER INTERFACE
Swipe right if you like the topic of an article (and you'll see more articles on this topic over time). Swipe left if you find the topic boring (and you'll see less). If you want to listen to your feed instead of reading, click a button (or say "listen"), and we'll play it for you. If you want to comment or share an item, it's just one button-click (or voice command) away, so you can help your friends be as informed as you are.

A BULLET-POINT SUMMARY FOR EACH NEWS ITEM
Save time and effort by reading a few short bullet points instead of giant walls of text. Most articles don't need to be 8000 words. We summarize them for you in a few sentences (and then link to the source).

A NUTRITION LABEL FOR EACH NEWS ITEM
Your food comes with nutrition labels, and now your news does too. Every article in your feed comes with a detailed nutrition label that helps you decide whether it's worth consuming before you consume it.

HANDS-FREE NEWS READING
Use voice commands to control your feed, and ask to listen to news articles instead of reading them. All the slick interface features described above - swipes, customizations, etc - can be done hands-free!

Read the best news the internet has to offer and stay in control of your news feed, using the latest AI science & advanced tech from Austin, Texas.

It's free, ad-free, and junk-free.

Try it out for yourself, completely free of charge.
